        { "x": 29, "y": 9, "to_map": "mere_shallows", "to_x": 1, "to_y": 9 }
      ],
      "npcs": [
        {
          "id": "lockkeeper_dagny",
          "x": 20,
          "y": 6,
          "name": "Lockkeeper Dagny",
          "dialogue": [
            {
              "when": { "relapsed": ["the_font", true] },
              "lines": [
                "The weir gauges jumped last night. Warm outflow, steady pulse — that's not weather, that's a pump.",
                "The Font is drawing again and my lock gates are a hundred years of rust. Whatever you did out there, it needs doing twice."
              ]
            },
            {
              "when": { "verdict": ["the_font", "Purge"] },
              "lines": [
                "Outflow's stone cold. First winter the weir hasn't steamed since my grandmother kept it.",
                "Half the town toasted you. The other half checked their nets, found them empty, and went to bed early. Both halves were right."
              ]
            },
            {
              "when": { "verdict": ["the_font", "Reseed"] },
              "lines": [
                "The water coming through my gates runs warm and full of fry — wild fry, thrown, not decanted.",
                "A lock only works if what's upstream means well. For the first time in my family's book, I get to write that it does."
              ]
            },
            {
              "when": { "verdict": ["the_font", "Bind"] },
              "lines": [
                "So the Font answers to you. I keep the weir, so I'll say this plain, keeper to keeper:",
                "every gate holds fine right up until the day someone wants it open more than you want it shut. Sleep near your levers."
              ]
            },
            {
              "lines": [
                "Saltwick was built on stilts because our grandmothers didn't trust the shore, and the shore has never once earned better.",
                "The weir keeps the drowned quarter drowned. The Font keeps its own counsel at the end of the causeway east of here.",
                "Buy what you need at the post. Folk who walk toward the Font underloaded come back overboard, if they come back."
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "cob",
          "x": 8,
          "y": 11,
          "name": "Cob",
          "dialogue": [
            {
              "when": { "verdict": ["the_font", "Purge"] },
              "lines": [
                "The lake stopped humming. I used to fall asleep to it.",
                "Gran says good riddance. But she sits up listening now, same as me."
              ]
            },
            {
              "when": { "verdict": ["the_font", "Reseed"] },
              "lines": [
                "There are otter pups under the pier! Six! I named all of them, and two of the names are secret.",
                "Gran says the mere's forgiven us. I didn't know it was us who did something."
              ]
            },
            {
              "lines": [
                "I found a glass jar on the beach with a whole tiny town inside. Gran made me throw it back.",
                "She says everything the water gives you, it's only lending. Even the Axolet that follows my skiff. ESPECIALLY the Axolet."
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
