      "npcs": [
        {
          "id": "diver_maren",
          "x": 7,
          "y": 4,
          "name": "Diver Maren",
          "dialogue": [
            {
              "when": { "flags_none": ["mirrormere_gift"] },
              "lines": [
                "Hold up. You're walking at those doors, which makes you either the rider Saltwick keeps praying about or the next thing I fish out of the shallows.",
                "I cut this gland off a war-unit that's been asleep under the causeway since before names. It still sighs when it's warm. Take it — it wants to work, and I want to stop hearing it."
              ],
              "set_flags": ["mirrormere_gift"],
              "give_grafts": ["geyser_gland"]
            },
            {
              "when": { "relapsed": ["the_font", true] },
              "lines": [
                "I was under the causeway an hour ago. The intake grates are turning again, slow, like something stretching in its sleep.",
                "Whoever restarted the Font didn't drain the halls first. Everything you left alive down there is awake, armed, and wet."
              ]
            },
            {
              "when": { "verdict": ["the_font", "Purge"] },
              "lines": [
                "I dove the outfall after you silenced it. Forty years of salvage down there and I couldn't take any of it.",
                "It's a graveyard now, a real one. You don't strip a graveyard. You just surface quiet and stop telling people what's below."
              ]
            },
            {
              "when": { "verdict": ["the_font", "Reseed"] },
              "lines": [
                "The drowned quarter has fish in the windows now. Balenu calves nose through the old streets like they're reading them.",
                "The ruins didn't get less sad, exactly. They got lived in. Maybe that's the only mercy ruins are owed."
              ]
            },
            {
              "when": { "verdict": ["the_font", "Bind"] },
              "lines": [
                "The intake current changed the day you bound it. It pulls toward you now. I've felt it on every dive since.",
                "I'm not saying it's wrong. I'm saying I used to salvage from the last people the Font obeyed, and none of them thought it was wrong either."
              ]
            },
            {
              "lines": [
                "That's the Font. It filtered a city's water once — then the war came, and someone taught it to filter out everything except soldiers.",
                "The doors have been sealed since the drowning. The lakes stayed clear all these years because it never stopped straining them. Kill it, and you'll finally learn what it's been holding back.",
                "Whole streets are down there under the causeway. When the water's still, you can see the lamp posts. Don't look too long — divers who look too long start counting the doors."
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
